+# Jupyter AI Version Fix
+
+## Issue
+
+There is a compatibility issue with Jupyter AI 2.31.0 when using the amazon-sagemaker-jupyter-ai-q-developer extension. The Q chat feature is not loading correctly, and users are unable to get responses back from Q.
+
+The error occurs because Jupyter AI 2.31.0 introduced a breaking change where the `embeddings_fields` field became required in the `GlobalConfig` class, but existing configurations might not have this field.
+
+Error message:
+```
+E 2025-03-24 22:06:57.966 ServerApp] Uncaught exception GET /jupyterlab/default/api/ai/config?1742854017897 (169.255.255.1)
+    
+ method='GET', uri='/jupyterlab/default/api/ai/config?1742854017897', version='HTTP/1.1', remote_ip='169.255.255.1')
+    Traceback (most recent call last):
+      File "/opt/conda/lib/python3.11/site-packages/tornado/web.py", line 1788, in _execute
+        result = method(*self.path_args, **self.path_kwargs)
+                 ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
+      File "/opt/conda/lib/python3.11/site-packages/tornado/web.py", line 3301, in wrapper
+        return method(self, *args, **kwargs)
+               ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
+      File "/opt/conda/lib/python3.11/site-packages/jupyter_ai/handlers.py", line 534, in get
+        config = self.config_manager.get_config()
+                 ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
+      File "/opt/conda/lib/python3.11/site-packages/jupyter_ai/config_manager.py", line 458, in get_config
+        config = self._read_config()
+                 ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
+      File "/opt/conda/lib/python3.11/site-packages/jupyter_ai/config_manager.py", line 276, in _read_config
+        config = GlobalConfig(**raw_config)
+                 ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
+      File "/opt/conda/lib/python3.11/site-packages/pydantic/main.py", line 214, in __init__
+        validated_self = self.__pydantic_validator__.validate_python(data, self_instance=self)
+                         ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
+    pydantic_core._pydantic_core.ValidationError: 1 validation error for GlobalConfig
+    embeddings_fields
+      Field required [type=missing, input_value={'model_provider_id': 'am...completions_fields': {}}, input_type=dict]
+        For further information visit https://errors.pydantic.dev/2.10/v/missing
+```
+
+## Solution
+
+The simplest solution is to pin the version of Jupyter AI to 2.30.0, which doesn't have this requirement.
+
+### How to Fix
+
+1. Run the provided script to install the correct version:
+   ```
+   python fix_jupyter_ai_version.py
+   ```
+
+2. Alternatively, you can manually install the correct version:
+   ```
+   pip install jupyter-ai==2.30.0
+   ```
+
+This will downgrade Jupyter AI to version 2.30.0, which is compatible with the amazon-sagemaker-jupyter-ai-q-developer extension.
+
+## Alternative Solutions
+
+If you need to use Jupyter AI 2.31.0 or later, you would need to modify your configuration file to include the `embeddings_fields` field. This can be done by:
+
+1. Locating your Jupyter AI configuration file (typically at `~/.jupyter/jupyter_ai/config.json`)
+2. Adding the `embeddings_fields` field if it's missing:
+   ```json
+   {
+     "model_provider_id": "...",
+     "embeddings_provider_id": "...",
+     "send_with_shift_enter": false,
+     "fields": {},
+     "api_keys": {},
+     "completions_model_provider_id": "...",
+     "completions_fields": {},
+     "embeddings_fields": {}
+   }
+   ```
+
+However, the recommended approach is to pin the version to 2.30.0 until a proper fix is available.
